4. ERROR BOUNDARIES
================================================================================

FINDINGS:

[MEDIUM] ErrorBoundary uses emoji "⚠️" in the fallback UI (line 33).
  Per design guidelines, emoji should not be used in application UI.

[MEDIUM] ErrorBoundary fallback has a "تسجيل دخول جديد" button that calls
  localStorage.clear() (line 49). This is a nuclear option that clears ALL
  localStorage data including offline data, cached credentials, etc. Should
  only clear auth-related keys.

[GOOD] Dual error boundaries in App.tsx - outer one wraps entire app, inner one
  wraps the route content. This prevents total app crash on route-level errors.

[GOOD] ErrorBoundary shows error details only in development mode.

[CONCERN] No error boundary wrapping individual Suspense boundaries. If a lazy
  component fails to load (e.g., network error during chunk fetch), the error
  propagates up to the nearest ErrorBoundary which is at the App level, causing
  the entire app to show the error state rather than just the affected page.

