9. OFFLINE/SYNC COMPONENTS AUDIT
================================================================================

FINDINGS:

[HIGH] App.tsx Router component (lines 118-175): The useEffect for sync
  initialization uses Capacitor and PushNotifications without checking if
  those modules are available first. On web, `Capacitor.isNativePlatform()`
  should return false, but the import is at module level (line 427-428)
  which could cause issues if @capacitor/core isn't properly configured.

[MEDIUM] Multiple initialization points for IndexedDB:
  - main.tsx line 50: initializeDB().catch(console.error)
  - App.tsx line 122: await initializeDB()
  - App.tsx line 106: initializeStorage()
  This triple initialization is redundant and could cause race conditions.

[MEDIUM] The sync state subscription in Router (lines 144-166) creates a
  subscription but the cleanup function (line 168) is returned inside the
  async initSync function, not from the useEffect itself. This means the
  unsubscribe function is never actually called on unmount, causing a
  memory leak.

  Code:
    useEffect(() => {
      const initSync = async () => {
        // ...
        const unsubscribe = subscribeSyncState((state) => { ... });
        return () => unsubscribe();  // This return is inside async, not useEffect
      };
      initSync();  // The cleanup from async is ignored
    }, []);

[GOOD] SyncProgressTracker and PullToRefreshIndicator provide visual
  feedback for sync operations.
[GOOD] Offline API interceptor queues mutations when offline.

